cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use FormatShield in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "FormatShield: Pre-LLM Structural Gate Against Format-Based Prompt Injection in RAG Pipelines"
authors:
  - family-names: "Borkot Tulla"
    given-names: "MD Hamid"
    orcid: ""
version: "1.0.0"
date-released: "2026-04-28"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/hamidborkot/FormatShield"
abstract: >
  FormatShield is a pre-retrieval, format-aware structural gate that detects
  format-based prompt injection (FBPI) embedded in documents before they reach
  a large language model in a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) pipeline.
  It achieves F1=0.9750, Precision=1.0000, FPR=0.0000 on a 1,730-document
  benchmark, operates entirely offline (CPU-only, no LLM calls), and is
  statistically superior to all four baseline defenses (McNemar p<=0.0044).
keywords:
  - prompt injection
  - RAG security
  - format-based attack
  - LLM safety
  - document security
  - retrieval-augmented generation
preferred-citation:
